RTCGeometry rtcNewGeometry(
  RTCDevice device,
  enum RTCGeometryType type
);
.EE
.SS DESCRIPTION
Geometries are objects that represent an array of primitives of the same
type.
The \f[CR]rtcNewGeometry\f[R] function creates a new geometry of
specified type (\f[CR]type\f[R] argument) bound to the specified device
(\f[CR]device\f[R] argument) and returns a handle to this geometry.
The geometry object is reference counted with an initial reference count
of 1.
The geometry handle can be released using the
\f[CR]rtcReleaseGeometry\f[R] API call.
.PP
Supported geometry types are triangle meshes
(\f[CR]RTC_GEOMETRY_TYPE_TRIANGLE\f[R] type), quad meshes (triangle
pairs) (\f[CR]RTC_GEOMETRY_TYPE_QUAD\f[R] type), Catmull\-Clark
subdivision surfaces (\f[CR]RTC_GEOMETRY_TYPE_SUBDIVISION\f[R] type),
curve geometries with different bases
(\f[CR]RTC_GEOMETRY_TYPE_FLAT_LINEAR_CURVE\f[R],
\f[CR]RTC_GEOMETRY_TYPE_FLAT_BEZIER_CURVE\f[R],
.PD 0
.P
